Global Funds Buy Net 11.7 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-03-04T03:29:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/global-funds-buy-net-11-7-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 11.7
billion rupees ($259 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1 percent to 876.5 billion rupees, or 36
percent of gross market position, according to the exchangeâ€™s
website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on
Sept. 21.  Foreign investors bought a net 2.3 billion rupees of shares
in the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
